.TH CAP-WARN 8 "June 2026" "cap-alert 1.0.4" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
cap-alert \- NWS weather alert processor for AllStar/Asterisk nodes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cap-alert
[\fIcommand\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cap-alert
polls National Weather Service alerts and optional geo hazards, builds
ulaw audio with bundled sounds and text-to-speech, and plays announcements
on a configured AllStar node.
.PP
Scheduled polling is normally handled by \fBcap-alert.timer\fR (systemd), which runs
\fBcap-alert run\fR as the \fBasterisk\fR user.
.PP
The \fBcap-alert\fR wrapper accepts root invocation (\fBsudo cap-alert\fR) and re-executes
as \fBasterisk\fR; direct use requires the asterisk account.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B (none)
Run once manually (same as interactive test).
.TP
.B run
Scheduled invocation (used by \fBcap-alert.timer\fR).
.TP
.B doctor
Validate configuration, Asterisk connectivity, TTS backends, caches, and timer.
.SH FILES
/etc/cap-alert/config.php
.br
/var/lib/cap-alert/
.br
/var/log/cap-alert/cap-alert.log
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR cap-alert-configure (8),
.BR net-flag (8),
.BR cap-alert.timer (5)
